results %>%\n  select(Model, Accuracy, Kappa)\n\nprint(results_table)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.488238Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.49043Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.524734Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.522958Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"  Model  Accuracy     Kappa\n1   LDA 0.8075852 0.7783045\n2   KNN 0.8138239 0.7850050\n3   MLR 0.8496465 0.8261859\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":15},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The multnomial logistic regression model has the highest accuracy, withalpha = 1 and lambda = 0.0004906756 being the best fit.\n\n# Formatting the Submission file\n\nWe now create a data frame from the remaining 30% of the dataset.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"filenames_test_acc = list.files(\"./RawData/Test/\", \"^acc\", full.names = TRUE)\ntest_acc <- map_dfr(filenames_test_acc, extractTimeDomainFeatures, sample_labels)\n\nfilenames_test_gyro = list.files(\"./RawData/Test/\", \"^gyro\", full.names = TRUE)\ntest_gyro <- map_dfr(filenames_test_gyro, extractTimeDomainFeatures, sample_labels)\n\nmyTestData = test_acc %>% left_join(test_gyro, by = c('epoch', 'user_id', 'exp_id', 'activity', 'sampleid'))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.52741Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-09-24T18:14:35.528824Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-09-24T18:17:31.538769Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-09-24T18:17:31.536826Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"Warning message:\n“\u001b[1m\u001b[22mThere were 2 warnings in `summarise()`.\nThe first warning was:\n\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[36mℹ\u001b[39m In argument: `AR2_X2_lag2 = lagged_cor(X2, lag = 2)`.\n\u001b[36mℹ\u001b[39m In group 139: `epoch = 138`.\nCaused by warning in `cor()`:\n\u001b[33m!\u001b[39m the standard deviation is zero\n\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[36mℹ\u001b[39m Run `dplyr::last_dplyr_warnings()` to see the 1 remaining warning.”\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":16},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"We pre-process the test dataset in the same way as the training dataset using the preProcess() function again. Next, we use the predict() function to predict physical activity from the accelerator and gyrometer data. Finally, we save our predictions into a file named submission.csv.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# As a stand in for the actual test data we use the first 2550 rows from myData\n\n# Apply data transformation\nmyTestData2 = myTestData |> select(-c(\"epoch\",\"sampleid\",\"user_id\",\"exp_id\",\"sampleid\"))\nmyTestData2 = predict(preproc, myTestData2)\nmyTestData2 = myTestData2 |> select(-all_of(redundant))\n\n# Apply best model to predict activity\npredicted_activity = predict(fit_mlr, myTestData2)\n\n# Writing the test predictions to CSV file\nmyTestData |>\n\n    # Set `activity` to the predicted activity\n    mutate(activity = predicted_activity) |>\n\n    # prepend \"user\" and \"exp\" to user_id and exp_id\n    mutate(\n        user_id = paste(ifelse(user_id < 10, \"user0\", \"user\"), user_id, sep=\"\"), \n        exp_id = paste(ifelse(exp_id < 10, \"exp0\", \"exp\"), exp_id, sep=\"\")\n    ) |> \n\n    # unite columnes user_id, exp_id and sample_id into a string \n    # separated by \"_\" and store it in the new variable `Id`\n    unite(Id, user_id, exp_id, sampleid) |>\n\n    # retain only the `Id` and  predictions\n    select(Id, Predicted = activity) |>\n\n    # write to file\n    write_csv(\"submission.csv\")\n\n\n# Check the result: print first 20 lines in the submission file\ncat(readLines(\"submission.csv\",20), sep=\"\\n\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-09-24T18:17:31.543082Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-09-24T18:17:31.545171Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-09-24T18:17:32.158391Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-09-24T18:17:32.156397Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Id,Predicted\nuser02_exp03_0,-\nuser02_exp03_128,-\nuser02_exp03_256,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_384,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_512,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_640,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_768,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_896,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1024,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1152,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1280,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1408,-\nuser02_exp03_1536,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1664,STANDING\nuser02_exp03_1792,SITTING\nuser02_exp03_1920,SITTING\nuser02_exp03_2048,SITTING\nuser02_exp03_2176,SITTING\nuser02_exp03_2304,SITTING\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":17},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Divison of labour\n\nWe brainstormed ideas for feature extraction individually and later compiled our code.\nWe divided the writing of descriptions equally, but mostly worked together on the code when we could.","metadata":{}}]}